description: Tulsi has been found to help normalize blood sugar, blood pressure, and cholesterol levels. This makes it a good option for people with diabetes and heart-related conditions. It can reduce blood glucose and improve lipid profiles, supporting overall metabolic health.​
title: Tulsi can sharpen memory, boost metabolism, says American National Library of Medicine

description: An Indian employee's social media post about being placed on a Performance Improvement Plan (PIP) for refusing to work during his approved leave has sparked outrage online. The employee claimed his manager expected constant availability, even on weekends, and penalized him for prioritizing his time off.
title: What? Man refused to work during leaves, manager puts him on PIP

description: Following protests after the Pahalgam terror attack, right-wing groups demanded a boycott of Muslim vendors serving Vrindavan's Banke Bihari temple. However, the temple administration dismissed the call, emphasizing the significant contributions of Muslim artisans and weavers to the temple's traditions, including crafting deity attire and accessories. Local shopkeepers also expressed solidarity, highlighting the long-standing peaceful coexistence between the communities.
title: Why Banke Bihari temple dismissed ‘boycott Muslim trade’ call

description: In Bengaluru, a 16-year-old boy was allegedly targeted by a social media acquaintance and his accomplices, who stripped, filmed, and blackmailed him. The group coerced the boy into falsely confessing on video to capturing inappropriate images of girls and extorting money. The mother delayed reporting the incident, fearing for her son's safety, and suspects a female friend instigated the attack.
title: Bengaluru teen stripped, filmed and blackmailed by social media pal & gang

description: Pegatron, a major supplier to Apple and Tesla, cautions that Trump's tariff policies are creating confusion and potential shortages in the U.S. market. The fluctuating trade levies are disrupting global supply chains, forcing companies to rethink strategies. Prolonged tariffs could stifle innovation and increase consumer costs, impacting the tech sector.
title: Apple, Dell supplier warns of 'empty stores' in US on Trump tariffs

description: Infosys has recently asked 195 more trainees to leave after they failed internal assessments, bringing the total number of affected trainees to over 800 since February. The company is offering support, including outplacement services and training programs.
title: More layoffs! Infosys asks another batch of trainees to leave

description: The Supreme Court has decided against disclosing Pegasus reports that could compromise national security and sovereignty. While these sensitive reports will remain confidential, the court is considering informing individuals who suspect their phones were hacked. The decision aims to balance national security concerns with individual privacy rights, with the next hearing scheduled for July 30.
title: Pegasus row: SC says findings linked to national security will not be disclosed
Pro-Khalistani leader Jagmeet Singh gets emotional after defeat; internet cheers his fall

description: During the 2021 lockdown, Vaibhav Suryavanshi, a 10-year-old from Bihar, practiced cricket on his terrace. Four years later, at 14, he stunned the IPL by smashing the second-fastest century in just 35 balls. Vaibhav's journey highlights resilience, family sacrifices, and the power of dreams, proving that extraordinary talent can emerge from humble beginnings.
title: Vaibhav Suryavanshi: From training on a rooftop to creating IPL history

description: Mark Carney's Liberal Party is poised to form a minority government in Canada, presenting an opportunity to mend strained relations with India after a challenging period under Justin Trudeau. Carney has expressed interest in strengthening trade partnerships with India, particularly concerning the future of Indian students in Canada.
title: Visa, international students: What Carney's Canada election win means for India

description: Rajasthan Royals' batting coach Vikram Rathour lauded Vaibhav Suryavanshi, the 14-year-old sensation, after his record-breaking century in the IPL. Rathour believes Suryavanshi possesses exceptional talent and can serve Indian cricket for a long time with continued dedication. Gujarat Titans batter Sai Sudharsan also praised Suryavanshi's tremendous batting performance. Rathour expressed hope for RR's playoff chances, emphasizing the team's long-term vision.

description: Amazon launched its first 27 Project Kuiper satellites on April 29, 2025, aboard a ULA Atlas V rocket, marking its entry into the satellite broadband market. This $10 billion venture aims to provide global high-speed internet, especially to underserved areas. Amazon plans to deploy 3,236 satellites, competing with SpaceX's Starlink and integrating with AWS and its consumer ecosystem.
title: Amazon launches first Project Kuiper internet satellites into orbit: Report

description: In the 2025 Canadian federal election, the New Democratic Party, led by Jagmeet Singh, experienced a significant setback, plummeting to single-digit seat count and losing official party status. Prime Minister Mark Carney's Liberal Party secured a minority government amidst voter concerns over US-Canada relations. Following the results, Jagmeet Singh announced he would resign as party leader once an interim leader is appointed.

description: Vaibhav Suryavanshi, a 14-year-old, became the youngest centurion in men's T20 cricket, leading Rajasthan Royals to victory. His father, Sanjeev, inspired by Shubman Gill's story, built a cement pitch for Vaibhav's training. Coaches VVS Laxman and Rahul Dravid have mentored him, with Vikram Rathour praising his exceptional talent and technique, contributing to his rapid growth in the IPL.

description: BJP has strongly condemned Congress's 'Gayab' jibe, accusing them of using divisive imagery and inciting violence against PM Modi following the Pahalgam terror attack. BJP leaders criticized Congress for allegedly appealing to its Muslim vote bank and echoing the language of Pakistan.

description: Gold prices: Many financial advisors consider gold a dead investment that doesn’t generate any income or pay dividends. While that is true to some extent, gold is an excellent diversification tool because its price is not linked with other asset classes.

description: California is set to revamp its vehicle license plates in 2026, ending a nearly half-century-old format. The current sequence, a number followed by three letters and three numbers, is running out of combinations due to increased vehicle registrations. The new format will feature three numbers, three letters, and a final number.

description: Actor Ajith expressed profound sorrow over the Pahalgam terror attack, which killed 26 people, mostly tourists. He conveyed his heartfelt condolences to the victims' families and hoped for an end to such violence.

description: Following the deadly Pahalgam terror attack, Leader of Opposition Rahul Gandhi has urged Prime Minister Narendra Modi to convene a special session of Parliament. Gandhi emphasised the need for India to demonstrate unity and resolve against terrorism during this critical time. Mallikarjun Kharge, also requested a similar session, while earlier criticising the government's response to the attack, which claimed 26 lives.

description: Despite a recent terrorist attack in Pahalgam, tourists are still visiting Bhaderwah in Jammu and Kashmir. Visitors condemn the violence. One tourist praised the army's swift response during the attack in Pahalgam.

Truck drivers must speak English, Trump orders

description: Friedrich Merz is poised to become Germany's next chancellor on May 6, pending approvals from his party and the SPD. His recent policy U-turns, including debt brake reform and past alignment with the AfD, have alienated voters.

description: Fitness coach Ashley DiGiacomo Schwartz advises against weighing yourself after workouts, big meals, during your period, before bed, or after high-sodium/carb meals due to water weight fluctuations. description: Vaibhav Suryavanshi, a 14-year-old sensation, etched his name in IPL history with a breathtaking century for Rajasthan Royals against Gujarat Titans. description: Mark Carney's Liberal Party secured a historic victory in Canada's federal election, defying expectations. Donald Trump's tariff threats and nationalist rhetoric galvanized Canadian voters, who rallied around the Liberals as a defense against American aggression. description: A growing trend sees couples, dubbed "apartners," choosing separate homes despite commitment, challenging traditional cohabitation norms. description: Canadians went to the polls amidst a narrative dominated by Donald Trump's comments about Canada, overshadowing domestic issues. Poilievre's association with Trump proved a liability, while strategic voting patterns emerged in Atlantic Canada, reflecting the high stakes of the election.

description: India's high-emission industries, including aluminum, cement, and pulp & paper, face mandatory greenhouse gas emission intensity reduction targets starting 2025-26. The environment ministry's draft notification, covering 282 entities, introduces penalties for non-compliance. These industries will need to purchase carbon credits if they fail to meet the specified targets under the Carbon Credit Trading Scheme.

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah faced accusations of threatening a police officer during a Congress rally in Belagavi after BJP workers breached security and protested on stage. Siddaramaiah, visibly agitated, questioned the officer's actions and demanded the removal of the protesters while AICC general secretary Randeep Singh Surjewala and law and parliamentary affairs minister HK Patil tried to calm him.

description: Amidst BJP's criticism of Congress leaders questioning the necessity of conflict with Pakistan and challenging the Pahalgam victims' accounts, Congress has distanced itself from these statements. Jairam Ramesh clarified that individual remarks don't reflect the party's stance.

description: In a poignant assembly session, J&K CM Omar Abdullah vowed not to exploit the Pahalgam terrorist attack, which claimed 26 lives, for political gain. Visibly emotional, he condemned the attack and emphasized solidarity, rejecting demands to leverage the tragedy for statehood. National Conference president Farooq Abdullah asserted that Pakistan's actions had eliminated any possibility for dialogue.

description: The Karnataka High Court has established a Special Investigation Team (SIT) to investigate a data theft case at NewSpace Research and Technologies, a drone manufacturing company. description: A new study reveals that stronger, more unpredictable monsoons, driven by global warming, could devastate fish populations in the Indian Ocean. By analyzing ancient plankton shells, researchers found that past monsoon extremes led to collapses in marine productivity in the Bay of Bengal. These disruptions, caused by altered river runoff and ocean stratification, threaten the region's vital fisheries.

description: In response to the Pahalgam attack, the Indian government has blocked 16 Pakistani YouTube channels, including prominent media outlets like Geo News and Dawn News. These channels are accused of spreading provocative content and a misleading narrative against India.

description: The government is planning subsidies for battery swapping stations to facilitate long-distance electric vehicle travel, particularly for buses and trucks. Initially, the subsidy will focus on these vehicles, along with two and three-wheelers, as car battery swapping standards are still being developed. This initiative aligns with the increasing adoption of EVs and the establishment of charging infrastructure along national highways.

description: The government has tasked IIT-Delhi with a sample survey of waqf properties due to severely lacking survey data, despite ongoing digitisation efforts. description: India briefed the Taliban regime about Pakistan's involvement in the Pahalgam attack, seeking international support against cross-border terrorism. This meeting highlights improving India-Taliban relations amidst escalating tensions between India and Pakistan, primarily due to Pakistan's alleged support for terrorist activities.

description: Sunny Deol's 'Jaat,' released in 2025 after the success of 'Gadar 2,' has seen a significant drop in box office collections. The film, also starring Randeep Hooda, earned only Rs. 62 lakhs on its third Monday, marking its lowest collection so far, bringing the total to Rs 85.62 crore.

Judge Surajit Mandal highlighted the failure to conduct forensic testing on key evidence like the bloodstained pillow and a cotton belt, the alleged murder weapons.

description: Investigations reveal Hashim Musa, the Pakistani terrorist behind the Pahalgam massacre, is a former para commando from Pakistan's special forces. Sources indicate Musa, now with LeT, was deployed to J&K to target non-locals and security forces.

description: Deteriorating Indo-Pak relations and heightened security concerns have drastically reduced medical visas issued to Pakistani nationals seeking treatment in India. From over 1,600 visas in 2016, the number plummeted to just over 200 in 2024, a trend exacerbated by events like the Kulbhushan Jadhav case and the Pulwama attack.

description: The Supreme Court overturned a woman's murder conviction for killing her two daughters in Chhattisgarh, citing a lack of intent due to a possible temporary mental disorder. description: A recent study reveals that cinnamon, a widely used spice, may interfere with certain medications by reducing their effectiveness. description: Amid escalating tensions between India and Pakistan following the Pahalgam terrorist attack, the United States has stated that it is in communication with both nations at various levels, urging them to pursue a responsible resolution.
